# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore
# Scope: plugins, core, magui, ci, deps (optional)
#
# Example: fix(plugins): handle missing sosreport files gracefully
# Example: feat(executor): add --profile flag for performance profiling
# Example: docs(templates): add PLUGIN_DEVELOPMENT.md tutorial
#
# --- COMMIT END ---
# Type can be:
#   feat     (new feature)
#   fix      (bug fix)
#   docs     (documentation)
#   style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#   refactor (refactoring production code)
#   perf     (performance improvement)
#   test     (adding tests, refactoring tests; no production code change)
#   build    (build system, dependencies)
#   ci       (CI/CD pipeline changes)
#   chore    (updating grunt tasks etc; no production code change)
#
# Subject should:
#   - Use imperative mood ("add feature" not "added feature")
#   - Not capitalize first letter
#   - Not end with a period
#
# Body should explain what and why vs. how (optional)
# Footer should reference issues (optional): "Fixes #123"
